OL,3,CWater company fined #350,000 after
OL,4,Cpumping station incident and sewage
OL,5,Cdischarge
OL,7,FOn 12 March 2018, the sewage pumping
OL,8,Fstation filled to the point where
OL,9,Ftelemetry alarms sounded, indicating a
OL,10,Fdischarge of sewage into Foss Dyke.
OL,11,FThe alarms were noted at Yorkshire
OL,12,FWater's control centre and attributed
OL,13,Fto high rainfall.
OL,15,FHigh rainfall was not a valid reason
OL,16,Fas the sewage pumping station was only
OL,17,Fallowed to discharge in an emergency
OL,18,Fas set out in its environmental permit
OL,19,Fand not, as with some water company
OL,20,Fassets like combined sewer overflows,
OL,21,Fin 'storm conditions'.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
