OL,3,CWater company fined #350,000 after
OL,4,Cpumping station incident and sewage
OL,5,Cdischarge
OL,7,FYorkshire Water did not attend the
OL,8,Fpumping station, despite the data
OL,9,Findicating a sewage spill.
OL,11,FTwo days later, on 14 March, Yorkshire
OL,12,FWater received a report from the
OL,13,Fpublic about a discharge of sewage
OL,14,Ffrom Fossbridge pumping station.
OL,16,FIt was found the main pump was running
OL,17,Fbut on 'low amps' - which indicates a
OL,18,Fpotential air lock - and the backup
OL,19,Fpump was still not repaired. Yorkshire
OL,20,FWater had no functioning pumps at the
OL,21,Fpumping station.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/9
